Preparation
------------

Copy the most recent library tar-file to SE on manno

cd cern_cvs/cmssw/CMSSW_1_3_1_HLT6/lib/slc3_ia32_gcc323
rm libAna00.so
cp ../../src/AnalysisDataFormats/HeavyFlavorObjects/lib/libAna00.so .
cd ../..

tar cvf - lib module src/HeavyFlavorAnalysis/Bs2MuMu/data/*.cf? | gzip > test.tar.gz
tar -tzf test.tar.gz
edg-gridftp-ls $GSIFTP/cms/local_tests/libHeavyFlavorAnalysisBs2MuMu.tar.gz
edg-gridftp-rm $GSIFTP/cms/local_tests/libHeavyFlavorAnalysisBs2MuMu.tar.gz

globus-url-copy file:/home/ceggel/cern_cvs/cmssw/CMSSW_1_3_1_HLT6/test.tar.gz $GSIFTP/cms/local_tests/libHeavyFlavorAnalysisBs2MuMu.tar.gz
globus-url-copy $GSIFTP/cms/local_tests/libHeavyFlavorAnalysisBs2MuMu.tar.gz file:/home/ceggel/cern_cvs/cmssw/CMSSW_1_3_1_HLT6/testMe.tar.gz

edg-gridftp-ls $GSIFTP/cms/local_tests/libHeavyFlavorAnalysisBs2MuMu.tar.gz

Modification
------------

Modify the template

- test-grid.jdl  --> storage element, directory on storage element, output filename, computing element
- test-grid.cfg  --> number of events

Job Creation
------------

Create all cfg/jdl for a certain channel (e.g. Bs2MuMu)
by running mkAll specifying the channel with the -d option.
As an example "./mkAll -d Bs2MuMu" (-p for dry run). This will

- check for all reskimmed sample on storage element in eggel/HLTrigger/Bs2MuMu
- make a cfg/jdl per availble sample and move it to ./Bs2MuMu
- copy the wrapper script runAnalysis.sh to ./Bs2MuMu

Job Submission
--------------

Test one of the jdl files:

gmat_ test-0001.jdl

Submit all jobs with 

#go (= ~/perl/grAll *.jdl, with -p option)
./re

Check job status with

./re -c

Submit jobs with

./re (-p to test)

Resubmit aborted jobs

./re -i

Job Output
----------

gbg ---> retrieves output sandbox
gbu ---> unmangles directory names










